evs.data.fileio
Class NetCDFFileIO

java.lang.Object
  evs.data.fileio.FileIO
      evs.data.fileio.NetCDFFileIO
All Implemented Interfaces:
InputDataIO
public class NetCDFFileIO
extends FileIO
implements InputDataIO

Reads one or more time-series files in the NetCDF. Reads both files containing ensemble forecasts and files containing observations. This class coordinates the reading of several files and stores the resulting data centrally.

Version:
1.0
Author:
evs@hydrosolved.com

NetCDFFileIO

public NetCDFFileIO(java.io.File[] files,
                    java.util.Vector<VUIdentifier> readMe,
                    java.util.TimeZone zone,
                    boolean forecastData,
                    ConditionArray conditions)
             throws java.io.IOException
Reads an array of file containing ensemble forecasts or observations. The data are then accessible via the instance methods. Throws an exception if the expected time zone does not match the time zone on file.

Parameters:
files - the files containing the ensemble forecasts
readMe - the data to read
zone - the time zone to check against the time zone on file
forecastData - is true if the data to be passed are forecasts, false for observations
conditions - an array of conditions upon which to restrict reading (may be null)
Throws:
java.io.IOException
